    <stitle>DT 466 / DT 570 / HT 570 Service Manual - 2004 Emissions with EGR - Crankcase, Crankshaft, and Camshaft -
        Installation - Oil Level Gauge
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc id="Svcproc0902" svcproctype="install" graphiccount="1">
        <title>Oil Level Gauge</title>
        <figure id="f2650941" figsize="pg-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figh06/h06082.cgm" type="cgm" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="484px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Oil level gauge assembly</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Bolt, M6 x 40</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Nut, M6</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Cushioned clamp</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Oil filler tube</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Tube clamp</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Oil level gauge tube</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Oil dipstick tube seal</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">If removed earlier, install the oil level gauge tube by first applying Loctite&#174; #277
                around entire circumference of tube and casting. Drive tube into crankcase until bead of tube is seated
                in chamfer of crankcase boss.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install a new oil dipstick tube seal between oil filler tube and crankcase oil tube
                flange.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the tube clamp at the crankcase.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the oil filler tube bolt (M6 x 40) and nut (M6) at the fuel filter bracket.</para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
